Note:
Runa Standard Library: OrderedDict (Ordered Dictionary)

Provides an ordered dictionary that maintains insertion order of keys, essential for AI-to-AI communication
where key order matters for reproducibility and deterministic behavior.

Advanced features include:
- Insertion order preservation
- Move to end operations (move_to_end, move_to_front)
- Ordered iteration and bulk operations
- Memory-efficient implementation
- Thread-safe operations (when supported)
:End Note

Type OrderedDict[K, V] is Dictionary with:
    items as List[Tuple[K, V]]
    lookup as Dictionary[K, Integer]
    capacity as Integer

Note: Core OrderedDict Operations
Process called "create_ordered_dict" that returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Return OrderedDict with:
        items as list containing
        lookup as dictionary with:
        capacity as 0

Process called "create_ordered_dict_from_pairs" that takes pairs as List[Tuple[Any, Any]] returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let od be create_ordered_dict
    For each pair in pairs:
        Let key be pair at index 0
        Let value be pair at index 1
        Set od to set with od as od and key as key and value as value
    Return od

Process called "set" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and key as Any and value as Any returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let items be od["items"]
    Let lookup be od["lookup"]
    If key in lookup:
        Let index be lookup[key]
        Let new_items be list containing
        For i from 0 to length of items:
            If i is equal to index:
                Add (key, value) to new_items
            Otherwise:
                Add items[i] to new_items
        Set items to new_items
    Otherwise:
        Add (key, value) to items
        Set lookup[key] to length of items minus 1
        Set od["capacity"] to length of items
    Return dictionary with:
        items as items
        lookup as lookup
        capacity as od["capacity"]

Process called "get" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and key as Any returns Any:
    Let lookup be od["lookup"]
    If key in lookup:
        Let index be lookup[key]
        Let items be od["items"]
        Let pair be items[index]
        Return pair at index 1
    Throw KeyError with message "Key not found"

Process called "get_safe" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and key as Any and default as Any returns Any:
    Let lookup be od["lookup"]
    If key in lookup:
        Let index be lookup[key]
        Let items be od["items"]
        Let pair be items[index]
        Return pair at index 1
    Return default

Process called "remove" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and key as Any returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let lookup be od["lookup"]
    If key in lookup:
        Let index be lookup[key]
        Let items be od["items"]
        Let new_items be list containing
        Let new_lookup be dictionary with:
        For i from 0 to length of items:
            If i is not equal to index:
                Let pair be items[i]
                Let pair_key be pair at index 0
                Let pair_value be pair at index 1
                Add pair to new_items
                Set new_lookup[pair_key] to length of new_items minus 1
        Return dictionary with:
            items as new_items
            lookup as new_lookup
            capacity as length of new_items
    Throw KeyError with message "Key not found"

Process called "remove_safe" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and key as Any returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let lookup be od["lookup"]
    If key in lookup:
        Return remove with od as od and key as key
    Return od

Process called "pop" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and key as Any returns (OrderedDict[Any, Any], Any):
    Let lookup be od["lookup"]
    If key in lookup:
        Let index be lookup[key]
        Let items be od["items"]
        Let pair be items[index]
        Let value be pair at index 1
        Let new_od be remove with od as od and key as key
        Return (new_od, value)
    Throw KeyError with message "Key not found"

Process called "pop_safe" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and key as Any and default as Any returns (OrderedDict[Any, Any], Any):
    Let lookup be od["lookup"]
    If key in lookup:
        Let index be lookup[key]
        Let items be od["items"]
        Let pair be items[index]
        Let value be pair at index 1
        Let new_od be remove with od as od and key as key
        Return (new_od, value)
    Return (od, default)

Process called "pop_last" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns (OrderedDict[Any, Any], Any):
    Let items be od["items"]
    If length of items is equal to 0:
        Throw IndexError with message "OrderedDict is empty"
    Let last_pair be items at index length of items minus 1
    Let last_key be last_pair at index 0
    Let last_value be last_pair at index 1
    Let new_od be remove with od as od and key as last_key
    Return (new_od, last_value)

Process called "pop_first" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns (OrderedDict[Any, Any], Any):
    Let items be od["items"]
    If length of items is equal to 0:
        Throw IndexError with message "OrderedDict is empty"
    Let first_pair be items[0]
    Let first_key be first_pair at index 0
    Let first_value be first_pair at index 1
    Let new_od be remove with od as od and key as first_key
    Return (new_od, first_value)

Note: Query and Analysis Operations
Process called "contains" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and key as Any returns Boolean:
    Let lookup be od["lookup"]
    Return key in lookup

Process called "size" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns Integer:
    Let items be od["items"]
    Return length of items

Process called "is_empty" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns Boolean:
    Return size with od as od is equal to 0

Process called "keys" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let items be od["items"]
    Let result be list containing
    For each pair in items:
        Let key be pair at index 0
        Add key to result
    Return result

Process called "values" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let items be od["items"]
    Let result be list containing
    For each pair in items:
        Let value be pair at index 1
        Add value to result
    Return result

Process called "items" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns List[Tuple[Any, Any]]:
    Let items be od["items"]
    Return copy with lst as items

Process called "get_first_key" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns Any:
    Let items be od["items"]
    If length of items is equal to 0:
        Throw IndexError with message "OrderedDict is empty"
    Let first_pair be items[0]
    Return first_pair at index 0

Process called "get_last_key" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns Any:
    Let items be od["items"]
    If length of items is equal to 0:
        Throw IndexError with message "OrderedDict is empty"
    Let last_pair be items at index length of items minus 1
    Return last_pair at index 0

Process called "get_first_value" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns Any:
    Let items be od["items"]
    If length of items is equal to 0:
        Throw IndexError with message "OrderedDict is empty"
    Let first_pair be items[0]
    Return first_pair at index 1

Process called "get_last_value" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns Any:
    Let items be od["items"]
    If length of items is equal to 0:
        Throw IndexError with message "OrderedDict is empty"
    Let last_pair be items at index length of items minus 1
    Return last_pair at index 1

Note: Order Manipulation Operations
Process called "move_to_end" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and key as Any returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let lookup be od["lookup"]
    If key in lookup:
        Let index be lookup[key]
        Let items be od["items"]
        Let pair be items[index]
        Let new_items be list containing
        For i from 0 to length of items:
            If i is not equal to index:
                Add items[i] to new_items
        Add pair to new_items
        Let new_lookup be dictionary with:
        For i from 0 to length of new_items:
            Let new_pair be new_items[i]
            Let new_key be new_pair at index 0
            Set new_lookup[new_key] to i
        Return dictionary with:
            items as new_items
            lookup as new_lookup
            capacity as od["capacity"]
    Return od

Process called "move_to_front" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and key as Any returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let lookup be od["lookup"]
    If key in lookup:
        Let index be lookup[key]
        Let items be od["items"]
        Let pair be items[index]
        Let new_items be list containing
        Add pair to new_items
        For i from 0 to length of items:
            If i is not equal to index:
                Add items[i] to new_items
        Let new_lookup be dictionary with:
        For i from 0 to length of new_items:
            Let new_pair be new_items[i]
            Let new_key be new_pair at index 0
            Set new_lookup[new_key] to i
        Return dictionary with:
            items as new_items
            lookup as new_lookup
            capacity as od["capacity"]
    Return od

Process called "reverse" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let items be od["items"]
    Let reversed_items be reverse with lst as items
    Let new_lookup be dictionary with:
    For i from 0 to length of reversed_items:
        Let pair be reversed_items[i]
        Let key be pair at index 0
        Set new_lookup[key] to i
    Return dictionary with:
        items as reversed_items
        lookup as new_lookup
        capacity as od["capacity"]

Note: Bulk Operations
Process called "clear" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Return dictionary with:
        items as list containing
        lookup as dictionary with:
        capacity as 0

Process called "copy" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let items be od["items"]
    Let lookup be od["lookup"]
    Let capacity be od["capacity"]
    Let new_items be list containing
    For each pair in items:
        Add pair to new_items
    Let new_lookup be dictionary with:
    For each key and value in lookup:
        Set new_lookup[key] to value
    Return OrderedDict with:
        items as new_items
        lookup as new_lookup
        capacity as capacity

Process called "update" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and other as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let other_items be other["items"]
    Let result be od
    For each pair in other_items:
        Let key be pair at index 0
        Let value be pair at index 1
        Set result to set with od as result and key as key and value as value
    Return result

Process called "update_from_dict" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and other as Dictionary[Any, Any] returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let result be od
    For each key and value in other:
        Set result to set with od as result and key as key and value as value
    Return result

Note: Filtering and Transformation Operations
Process called "filter_keys" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and predicate as Process returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let items be od["items"]
    Let new_items be list containing
    For each pair in items:
        Let key be pair at index 0
        If predicate with key as key:
            Add pair to new_items
    Let new_lookup be dictionary with:
    For i from 0 to length of new_items:
        Let pair be new_items[i]
        Let key be pair at index 0
        Set new_lookup[key] to i
    Return dictionary with:
        items as new_items
        lookup as new_lookup
        capacity as length of new_items

Process called "filter_values" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and predicate as Process returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let items be od["items"]
    Let new_items be list containing
    For each pair in items:
        Let value be pair at index 1
        If predicate with value as value:
            Add pair to new_items
    Let new_lookup be dictionary with:
    For i from 0 to length of new_items:
        Let pair be new_items[i]
        Let key be pair at index 0
        Set new_lookup[key] to i
    Return dictionary with:
        items as new_items
        lookup as new_lookup
        capacity as length of new_items

Process called "map_keys" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and transform as Process returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let items be od["items"]
    Let new_items be list containing
    For each pair in items:
        Let key be pair at index 0
        Let value be pair at index 1
        Let new_key be transform with key as key
        Add (new_key, value) to new_items
    Let new_lookup be dictionary with:
    For i from 0 to length of new_items:
        Let pair be new_items[i]
        Let key be pair at index 0
        Set new_lookup[key] to i
    Return dictionary with:
        items as new_items
        lookup as new_lookup
        capacity as length of new_items

Process called "map_values" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] and transform as Process returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let items be od["items"]
    Let new_items be list containing
    For each pair in items:
        Let key be pair at index 0
        Let value be pair at index 1
        Let new_value be transform with value as value
        Add (key, new_value) to new_items
    Let new_lookup be dictionary with:
    For i from 0 to length of new_items:
        Let pair be new_items[i]
        Let key be pair at index 0
        Set new_lookup[key] to i
    Return dictionary with:
        items as new_items
        lookup as new_lookup
        capacity as length of new_items

Note: Utility Operations
Process called "to_dict" that takes od as OrderedDict[Any, Any] returns Dictionary[Any, Any]:
    Let items be od["items"]
    Let result be dictionary with:
    For each pair in items:
        Let key be pair at index 0
        Let value be pair at index 1
        Set result[key] to value
    Return result

Process called "from_dict" that takes d as Dictionary[Any, Any] returns OrderedDict[Any, Any]:
    Let od be create_ordered_dict
    For each key and value in d:
        Set od to set with od as od and key as key and value as value
    Return od 